<section class="page-hero reveal">
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Our Adoption Process</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">
      A clear, careful placement process designed to protect every puppy and
      support prepared families.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="page-content reveal">
  <div class="container narrow reveal">
    <p>
      The ImperialPaws process is intentionally measured. Families can browse,
      apply, track status, and receive an invoice only after approval. This keeps
      communication organized and helps prevent rushed or confusing placements.
    </p>

    <div class="process-grid">
      <div class="process-card">
        <strong>1. Browse</strong>
        <p>Review photos, status, care notes, and profile details before applying.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="process-card">
        <strong>2. Apply</strong>
        <p>Submit one accurate application for the puppy you are interested in.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="process-card">
        <strong>3. Track</strong>
        <p>Use your private tracking code to follow review status and next steps.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2>1. Browse Available Puppies</h2>
    <p>
      Visitors are welcome to explore available, reserved, and sold puppies at
      any time. Each listing is designed to show current availability, photos,
      puppy details, and care information where available.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Submit an Adoption Application</h2>
    <p>
      When you find a puppy you are interested in, submit an application from
      that puppy's detail page. The form helps us learn about your household,
      location, and readiness for the breed.
    </p>
    <p>
      The system prevents the same buyer from repeatedly applying for the same
      puppy when the same email address or phone number is used.
    </p>

    <div class="notice-box">
      <p>
        Submitting an application does not guarantee approval, reserve a puppy,
        or create a payment obligation.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2>3. Application Review</h2>
    <p>
      Each application is reviewed individually. We may ask follow-up questions
      when more context is needed. Placement decisions are based on the puppy's
      welfare, timing, buyer preparedness, and overall fit.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Status Tracking</h2>
    <p>
      After submitting, you receive a tracking code. Keep it private and use it
      on the tracking page to view current status. Tracking helps avoid missed
      updates and keeps communication organized.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Approval and Invoice</h2>
    <p>
      If an application is approved, the admin can create a clear adoption
      invoice linked to that application. The invoice shows the puppy, buyer
      information, line item, amount, due date when used, and adoption note.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Final Placement Steps</h2>
    <p>
      After approval, we provide guidance for the next steps. Final placement
      remains subject to agreed arrangements, care expectations, and any written
      health or placement documentation provided by ImperialPaws.
    </p>

    <p class="closing-note">
      Thoughtful placements take time. A professional adoption process should
      feel organized, transparent, and centered on the puppy's long-term well-being.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
